.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-CHANNEL-COUNT" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-channel-count \- count channels grouped by state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-channel-count
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns the total channel count and a breakdown by state (e.g.\&
.BR CHANNELD_NORMAL ,
.BR CHANNELD_AWAITING_LOCKIN ,
etc.).
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"total":N,"by_state":{"CHANNELD_NORMAL":N,...}}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-list (1),
.BR lightning-channel-pending (1)
